did.abstract: Collection consists of black and white glass lantern slides of Western painting. Some materials relating to Italian Renaissance painting located in the Yale University Art Gallery, 1100 Chapel Street, New Haven, Connecticut, 06520. For further detail, consult the Yale University Art Gallery location listing at the end of this finding aid.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Copyright has not been transferred to Yale University. Further use of this material may be subject to the copyright laws of the United States (Title 17, United States Code) or to site license or other rights management terms or conditions.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Painting Lantern Slide Collection, Arts Library, Yale University.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Collection consists of black and white glass lantern slides of Western painting. Some materials relating to Italian Renaissance painting located in the Yale University Art Gallery, 1100 Chapel Street, New Haven, Connecticut, 06520. For further detail, consult the Yale University Art Gallery location listing at the end of this finding aid.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Arranged alphabetically by nationality individual artist name. Sub-divided primarily by location of the work. Some sections are preceded by an Anonymous grouping arranged chronologically.
